This is an R Markdown document. Markdown is a simple formatting syntax for authoring HTML, PDF, and MS Word documents. For more details on using R Markdown see http://rmarkdown.rstudio.com.

When you click the Knit button a document will be generated that includes both content as well as the output of any embedded R code chunks within the document. You can embed an R code chunk like this: # Set up data frame of monthly components

# Set path to target directory
setwd("C:/Home/Projects/GLWaterBudget/Analysis/Superior")

# source script to set up data files
source("Superior/src/work/setupMonthlyDataFrame.R")

## locfit 1.5-9.1    2013-03-22

You can also embed plots, for example:

Note that the echo = FALSE parameter was added to the code chunk to prevent printing of the R code that generated the plot.
